President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the violence that occurred on January 21, 2023, in Monterey Park, California. This order applies to the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all federal government facilities in the District of Columbia, as well as throughout the United States and its territories and possessions. The flag will remain at half-staff until sunset on January 26, 2023. Additionally, the flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same duration at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The order was signed on January 22, 2023, by President Joseph R. Biden Jr.